title: Domino Paper, 1928-2-76, 1745–60
creditline: Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt
description: Rectangular pieced portion of a sheet, with paired checkered serpentine bands, colored blue, entwined by serpentine bands of small flowers periodically set with larger rose-like flowers, colored pink and blue. Field white, with groundwork of black broken lines. White margin on one long and two short sides.
